Sentencas: Homogeneous nanocrystalline NiOCe0.9Ln0.1O2 (Ln=La, Sm, Gd, and Pr) composite anode and nanocrystalline Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 electrolyte material have been successfully synthesized by citrate precursor method.
Titulo: Low Temperature Electrode Materials Synthesized by Citrate Precursor Method for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: LSCF has been synthesized by conventional solid state method and used as cathode material in our studies.
Titulo: Low Temperature Electrode Materials Synthesized by Citrate Precursor Method for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The synthesized powders have been characterized by powder X-ray diffraction, microscopy, and surface area studies.
Titulo: Low Temperature Electrode Materials Synthesized by Citrate Precursor Method for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The average crystallite size of the anode materials has been found to be in the range of 515nm by HRTEM.
Titulo: Low Temperature Electrode Materials Synthesized by Citrate Precursor Method for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Highly dense electrolyte and porous electrode materials have been observed by FESEM and confirmed by BET surface area studies.
Titulo: Low Temperature Electrode Materials Synthesized by Citrate Precursor Method for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Three cells have been fabricated successfully.
Titulo: Low Temperature Electrode Materials Synthesized by Citrate Precursor Method for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Based on the performance of the three cells containing three different anode materials we have achieved better electrochemical characteristics in NiGDC with maximum power density of 302mWcm2 and open circuit voltage of 1.012V at 500 degrees C. The difference in the performance of the cells containing NiGDC as compared to NiLDC and NiSDC anode is due to changes in the microstructure and crystallite size of anode which affects the electrochemical performance of the cells.
Titulo: Low Temperature Electrode Materials Synthesized by Citrate Precursor Method for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The performances of all the cells containing nanocomposite powders are suitable anode materials for low temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Low Temperature Electrode Materials Synthesized by Citrate Precursor Method for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
